article.headline: Texas St. 80, Texas-Pan American 70
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- Cameron Johnson had 24 points and 10 rebounds for a double-double as Texas State beat Texas Pan-American 80-70 Saturday. Johnson hit 11 of 14 from the field. J.B. Conley came off the bench to add 11 points for Texas State (3-5). John Bowman and Uriel Segura added 10 points each, and Bowman hit 2 of 3 from 3-point range. Jared Maree had 20 points to lead Texas-Pan American (1-8). ChaRunn Jones and Ben Smith came off the bench to contribute 12 points each, including 4 of 6 3-pointers by Jones. The Bobcats committed 30 turnovers while forcing 17, and UTPA converted the Texas State miscues for 29 points. Texas State scored 13 points off of turnovers but outrebounded the Broncs 40-25. The Bobcats shot 57 percent while holding UTPA to 39 percent.
